s a part of it, but twice in five minutes? Seems steep. Ended up loosing a whole yellow bar of exp.<br><br>Still prefer grouping. Better exp in paw than outside, and a tank to take the hits for me. Still soloing is a necessity sometimes. Still waiting on that AoE snare so I can kite properly.<br><br>Advice welcomed. <p>Yours in Blood,<p><img src="http://www.v-d-p.net/sigs/ravensig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushizzanidiot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShizzaNidiot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/02 1:55:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> I tried root nuking at 4th level.  Died alot.<br><br>Tried it again I think maybe around 12th lvl.  Died alot then too.<br><br>22d?  Died.  Alot.<br><br>35?  Have I said that I died alot doing root/nuke?<br><br>Just never panned out for me.  I mostly grouped to 29th lvl, or kited mobs that were naturally slow (bugs, freeport, field of bone, north karana, etc), until 29th lvl.  Then the real exp started.<br><br>Luck to ya, maybe someone else out there has done the root/nuke thing to success, but for me, it was fantasy.<br><br>Shizz<br> <p>Shizza Nidiot58th Companion to the Chetari Rats of Dragon Necropolis(Don't ask, it's a long story)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usunsear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunsear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/02 2:35:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> <br>Well it's been a _long_ time ago, but this wizard did the mid-twenties in the gorge on evil eyes...  Dangerous business, but the root/nuke tactic was the core of it, and it did provide decent solo experience. <p><p align="center"><font face="Arial Narrow" color="#FFFFFF" size="1">ThinkGandolf and Aragorn... only they hate each other.</font></p><p align="center" style="margin-top: -15; margin-bottom: -15"><img border="0" src="http://www.arcanestrength.com/images/XienSig.jpg" width="557" height="150"></p><p align="center" style="margin-top: 15; margin-bottom: -15"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial Narrow" size="2">Xien60th Sorcerer of Solusek Ro&nbsp; -&nbsp; Torakk Swiftwynd 53rd Pathfinder ofTunare&nbsp; -&nbsp; Thelnar Ironheart 54th Cleric of Brell</font></p><p align="center" style="margin-top: 15; margin-bottom: -15"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial Narrow" size="2">Co-Leaderof </font><a href="http://www.arcanestrength.com"><i><font face="Arial Narrow" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">ArcaneStrength</font></i></a><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial Narrow" size="2"> onthe </font><a href="http://www.ayonae.ro"><font face="Arial Narrow" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">AyonaeRo</font></a><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial Narrow" size="2"> Server</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=finiel>Finiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/02 3:26:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> I have had some success with root/nuke, I still use it at 40 sometimes. The real key to soloing is target selection. You probably want to shoot for things that are a couple of levels lower. Resists are much less of a problem with mid blues than with high blues.<br><br>Bad luck probably played a role in your problems too. If you find you are having resist or fizzle problems, you should bail out of the fight, even if it just started. Regrouping beats corpse recovery. I didn't have many deaths, but there were times I had to gate away. I had a lot of practice casting between enemy swings from previous characters too.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uravensloche.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravensloche</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/02 5:08:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.crosswinds.net/~jester43615/wizard2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> These were high blues, most of them. When i was grouped at the spires at 27, they were even. so it was a 28 taking on a 27. That would explain a lot.<br><br>Will try rooks at kfc to get 29 tonight if i can't get a group. they hit less hard then those gnolls, less attacks too. Thanks.<br><br>(heh. This is my first character, much less caster. Even with greens, i still need to practice in between swings, though i am getting better at it)<br><br>Thanks for the advice, will see how it works out. <p>Yours in Blood,<p><img src="http://www.v-d-p.net/sigs/ravensig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 6:30:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I used root/nuke well into my 40's. I would pull with Flux staff, and high-tail it to my safe-spot for the area, then root the mob as soon as it was in range. Then I would back off to maximum DD range and start nuking. When root broke, I would generally stun (if it was a stunnable mob), re-root, and back to max DD distance again. Quite a lot more than you might expect form all the nasty things people have to say about root, it held through an entire fight, though the average was 2 roots per fight. The skin line of spells helped immensely. <p><table width = 30%><tr><td align=center style=filter:glow(color=#cc0000 strength=1)><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr><tr><td align=center><font size = -1><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=23437>~ <i>profile</i> ~</a></font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uravensloche.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravensloche</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 6:53:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.crosswinds.net/~jester43615/wizard2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> this is similar to what i tried, but with one problem. I did not have sow, or any other type of haste spell. Therefore i could not run to max distance till after the mob was rooted.<br><br>What i tried to do: Pull static gnoll spawn from spire with flux staff... immediately cast root. Root holds as mob is far enough away from spires to be out of aggro range of wandering mobs. Run to max distance, nuke, re-root as necessary.<br><br>What usually happened: Pull with flux staff, cast root. root is resisted mob reaches me, beats on leatherskin. re-root, get interrupted. reroot again, it holds. start running to max dd distance, root breaks, mob follows. stop to re-root, mob beats down rest of leatherskin and starts to do damage. get stunned while casting root. become unstunned, panic, try casting DD spells while in melee. Fail miserably. Wait while loading.<br><br>heh. Truth be told, it WAS the level of the mob that was my problem. I grouped last night in paw, asked group to let me experiment with the white gnolls (lower lvl then the tech mas ones). root held EVERY time. <br><br>Regardless, I got 29 last night, and bought BoF. Now i am going to go practice with it on REALLY low mobs so that I know what i'm doing weith it, then SLOWLY move up the lvl chain of mobs till i see it being resisted a bit. And i'm not trying anything risky till i get a death buffer. hehe. <p>Yours in Blood,<p><img src="http://www.v-d-p.net/sigs/ravensig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukalrieaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KalrieAF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 10:02:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> um, im uncertain as to why you would pull a mob with your Tstaff when you root / nuking.  Your first cast on a mob should be your bigest, baddest, slowest casting nuke spell you have.  Why you ask? Because its a free shot.  The mob has not agroed on you yet and is just standing there begging to be fried.  My point is, START the fight with the mob wounded.  If later in the fight it gets close, that one free nuke could make the difference between the mob running or you running =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukekenewah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kekenewah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 12:48:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I root nuked from 16 to 29, and only died once.  I usually tried to hunt near zone lines if possible in outdoor zones.  From 16-18 did NK.  From 18-23 did base of Kurns tower.  From 23-29 did LOIO.  I always pulled from maximum distance with nuke that allowed me to cast from farthest distance.  Then root, nuke, repeat till dead. Only rarely did I have SOW.  It was very dangerous and took much longer than it just took my monk twink to go thru same levels, but it can be done with correct target choice.  If I noticed something resisted roots I would find another type of mob.  I tried to avoid fast moving mobs. BoF at 29 was a godsend. <p>Kekenewah Silverbear <BR>Level 52 High Elf Wizard (01/22/02)<BR>Drinal server <BR>Order of the Silver Circle guild</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyahtzooba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yahtzooba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 2:10:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Approaching 44th and still root/nuke when soloing. BoF is truely a wonder! All that running around trying ta kite things wears my lil' butt out real quick, so I tend to work in a small triangle walking the target from point to point. If the target gets rooted, it is dead. If it breaks root, take the hit then root again. Many times I have charged the target to replace a broken root (if I wasnt far enough away for DD). Take the hit, then scorch its maggot-ridden hide.<br><br>When I was huntin the gnolls it seemed that quite often I would get an exceptionally strong one compared to the previous dozen I had roasted. It could be that you encountered a couple &quot;boosted&quot; critters! Also, it might be my imagination, but I swear all targets get tougher when you are close to Ding!<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://208.57.3.217/yaht/Boom41.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucumdar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cumdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/30/02 6:04:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Root&amp;Nuke</span><hr size=1> Next level you get BOF and everything changes.  I can usually kite with out SOW or Jboots.  SOW/boots is a must to multi-kite.<br><br>Root and nuke works ok, but root sucks and none of the upgrades until elnerick's is worth it's salt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utoxxthewizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toxx The Wizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/30/02 7:55:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root&amp;Nuke</span><hr size=1> Some mobs don't require snaring or sow/jboots.<br><br>If you strafe, you can actually out run a lot of mobs. (undead for example)<br><br>Hold right mouse button, and press forward + right/left at the same time.<br><br>This only works on some critters, so beware. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92172 "><IMG SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg2/fierios/Toxx.txt" HEIGHT=168 WIDTH=375></a></center><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/31/02 5:40:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root&amp;Nuke</span><hr size=1> The reason I pulled with flux staff was because in those days I liked to hunt busy areas. You can single pull much more readily with a non-damage means of aggro. Also, I pulled on the run to help avoid adds, and you can't nuke while running. I also didn't like to pull with BoF, because I wanted to get them to my safe spot as quickly as possible. Probably, I could have just nuked and killed most of them in place, but it would have taken more time to set up, watch pathing, etc. This way, once I had a good spot (or spots) for the area, I could hunt as fast as I could med. And yes, it did require SoW, and I spent lots on potions before I got my jboots. <p><table width = 30%><tr><td align=center style=filter:glow(color=#cc0000 strength=1)><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr><tr><td align=center><font size = -1><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=23437>~ <i>profile</i> ~</a></font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvincet1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vincet1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/31/02 1:46:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> I root nuked until lvl 29. Post 29 i kited all the way, course i had j boots at lvl 29 as well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>But root nuke works out well, just have to have mana to waste on root. At 16 i was doing beetle and griffawns in NK with root nuke, 5 maybe 6 nukes would kill a mob. Its pretty decent. At 20 I did this little gnome in lesser faydark and at 24 I did the osergan prisoner guy in High hold keep. All done root nuking, its rather easy. Skin line helps out alot too.<br><br>Silverblaze <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/02 11:47:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.totalnetsolutions.net/nightwatch/images/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> Pull w/ highest damage DD, root as soon as it starts to run towards you.  Use the lvl 4 root, cause it's the fastest casting at this time.  Immediately turn around and run til you're almost out of range.  Then DD it again, root again, if neccessary.  If root breaks, re-root, then run till you're almost out of range.<br><br>Moving away from gnolls is also a good idea, and definately don't pull with your SoTF unless you're kiting.  If you're root-nuking, then pull with lots of damage.  That first cast is your safest cast - use it to dish out everything you can. <p><center><img src="http://www.totalnetsolutions.net/nightwatch/images/aniar-sig.jpg" alt="Aniar Orrenson" hspace="10" vspace="10"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27902" target="_blank">Look down my pants with Magelo!</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uteamnoir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teamnoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/02 1:23:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> I have been root/nuking solo exclusively through my entire career so far.  (level 24 now).  I can often solo white and yellow, which seems to be more about mana capacity than anything else.<br><br>Awlin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usuleak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Suleak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/02 5:02:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> i dunno about the rest of you but if i cast my 39th root on a mob it sticks most of the time.. usually last decently long... then i nuke... it insta breaks 9 outta 10 times!... breaks others roots as well.. well this is at 44-48 that i noticed it... quite annoyin.. anywayz root... BoF them then woot screw sow <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  BoF then sowless kite not hard... if resisted... root... run back... BoF... nuke soem more !<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><EMBED src="http://members.aol.com/primesthfan/suleak.swf" quality=high wmode=transparent bgcolor=#FFFFFF  WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=125 TYPE="application/x-shockwave-flash" PLUGINSPAGE="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/index.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash"></EMBED><br>If you cant beat them... /Bonk them!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usinnjatorix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinnjatorix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 5:44:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://w1.853.telia.com/~u85304784/pics/eq/Sinnjatorix_luclin.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> My root / nuke success has been varying, sometimes enstill holds for 5 nukes next time it drops before button ungreys, died more then once over in OT where i have soloed around the mudhole, after i while i started to go for the mobs that run when low on hp.<br><br>Don't have SoTF staff or j/tboots and no sow, usually pull with lightning bolt for long range, can get a root off after that, resisted quite a bit, sometimes mob bolts the other way and i have to search for it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  also having 121 int makes my mana pool rather limited so resists or partly resists are bad for me, now that i dinged 24 problem is more noticable since the new spells cost a bit more to cast, spent all my mana killing a blue mob in marus seru <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>/Regards Berth <p>Sinnjatorix Soulburner human