e you root, you want to back up to the max nuking distance.  That way, if root breaks you have a fair chance of re-rooting before the mob gets to you.<br><br>As others pointed out, another key point is to picking the right target.   You want mobs a couple of levels lower than you to minimize resists.  If you find slow mobs, you have a good chance to out run them if things go poorly - beetles and undead are good choices.  Also, remember that not all mobs have the same resistances.<br><br>I think at 29 I soloed the bridge on the live side of Lower Guk, that was a great spot - decent loot and great experience. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unoonanie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Noonanie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/5/02 8:33:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> root/nuke is not really a great tactic after like lvl 20, imo.  just the way the whole system works.  the root line of spells weren't really designed for fighting... more of a defensive weapon, at least for wizards.  reason being... there's a resistance check at each time interval, as well as, each time the rooted mob is hit with any sort of dd or melee hit.  wizards have no other offensive capability.<br><br>additionally, root is a magic based spell.  warriors (which most mobs are designated as) have innate magic resistance, which not only makes it more difficult to stick... but at each resistance check, makes it easier to break.<br><br>not to mention, you waste mana by having to continually recast.  regardless of its small mana cost, it still uses up mana.  wizard's life blood is mana.  any waste is costly.<br><br>short and sweet... the root line of spells are just too unreliable to rely continuously on them.<br><br>get a group. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   or make sure you pick on mobs with low resists and don't hit hard.<br><br>and fyi.. you prolly meant you soloed the bridge in live side of lower guk at lvl 39 rather than lvl 29.  imo.. lvl 29 will get wasted there. multi pulls... zones too far away... too many resists.<br><br>Lasservien Leadbottom<br>Lotus Cult - Sorcerer<br>Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unoonanie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Noonanie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/5/02 8:40:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> <br>oh... and i dunno how far back the archives go... but there has been numerous, extraneously long posts concerning the root line of spells and their uses.  might wanna check them out if they're still around... good reading, <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>root/immobilize... for fighting... quick-er casting times... less mana cost ... short-er max duration.<br><br>enstill/para earth... for parking... slow-er casting times... more mana cost ... long-er max duration<br><br>fetter... sorta combo of both.<br><br>HOWEVER, says nothing as to how easily the spell will break.  mostly just dumb luck.<br><br>Lasservien Leadbottom<br>Lotus Cult - Sorcerer<br>Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=413.topic&start=21&stop=32>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=413.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=413.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=413.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=413.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=413.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=413.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" 